# Design System Standards

This project has a comprehensive design system documented in `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` at the repo root. Read it before making any visual or structural changes.

## Standing Rule: Document Every Design Decision

After implementing any visual, structural, or UX change, you MUST update this rule file and `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` with the new patterns, conventions, or components introduced. This ensures all future pages stay cohesive and aligned. Never skip this step.

## Quick Reference

### Colors
- **Warm accent** (`--accent-warm`): Amber `#D97706` in light, brighter in dark. Used for primary CTAs, section labels, icons, focus rings, hover borders.
- **Stage colors** (`--stage-1` through `--stage-5`): Warm-to-cool gradient (amber > orange > red-orange > rose > purple). Used in the IDEAL stepper (landing page) AND as page header accents in the docs.
- **Fumadocs tokens**: `fd-primary`, `fd-muted`, `fd-muted-foreground`, `fd-accent`, `fd-card`, `fd-border`, `fd-background`. Use these for all neutral/structural UI.
- **Rule**: No one-off hex values. All colors come from CSS custom properties in `app/global.css`.

### Typography
- **Display font**: Instrument Serif (class: `font-display`). Use for hero headings, section titles, pull quotes, stat callouts on marketing/landing pages, AND for the H1 page title on docs pages (via `docs-title` class).
- **Body font**: Inter (default, no class needed). Use for all body text, UI labels, nav, H2+ headings in docs, and all documentation body content.
- **No em dashes.** Never use `---` (em dash), `&mdash;`, or the Unicode em dash character. Use `--` instead.

### Docs Page Template (All 30 Content Pages)
Every docs page automatically gets these via the page template (`app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx`):
- **Stage-colored left border** on the header (amber for Stage 1, orange for Stage 2, etc.)
- **Instrument Serif H1 title** via `docs-title` class
- **Progress badge**: "Module X of 15" or "Stage N of 5" in stage color
- **Reading time estimate**: "X min read" computed from ToC section count
- **Progress bar**: thin colored bar showing position in the 15-module journey
- **Scroll progress**: fixed bar at viewport top showing reading position
- **Enhanced bottom navigation**: prev/next cards with title, description, and stage accent color
- **Progress gating**: pages are locked until the previous page is completed (85% scroll)

### Docs Content Patterns (MDX)
When editing content pages, use these Fumadocs components for visual richness:
- **`<Callout type="idea" title="...">`** -- for key concepts, core messages, framing statements
- **`<Callout type="info" title="...">`** -- for process explanations, cadences, rules
- **`<Cards>` + `<Card title="..." description="..." href="...">`** -- for linked navigation grids (personas, stage overviews, learning outcomes)
- **Bold labels** (`**Output for this module**`, `**Exercise:**`, `**Template**`) are auto-detected by the enhanced MDX `strong` component and rendered with icons and color highlights
- **Do not duplicate the H1 title** in the body. Fumadocs renders the frontmatter `title` as H1. Starting the body with `## Same Title` creates a redundant double heading.
- **Remove publisher metadata** from reader-facing pages (back cover copy, one-page pitches, stage maps for authors). If it's not useful to the reader, it doesn't belong.
- **Use `full: true`** in frontmatter when a page uses Cards or wide content that benefits from removing the max-width constraint on the docs body.

### Section Structure (Landing/Marketing Pages)
Every section follows this pattern:
- Uppercase label: `text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-fd-muted-foreground`
- Display title: `font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl`
- Content width: `max-w-5xl` (1280px)
- Horizontal padding: `px-6`
- Vertical padding: minimum `py-24 md:py-28`
- Alternate backgrounds between sections (`bg-fd-card` vs transparent)

### Buttons
- **Primary**: `bg-accent-warm` with dark foreground text. Rounded-lg, font-semibold. Subtle `hover:scale-[1.02]`.
- **Secondary**: `border border-fd-border` outlined. Rounded-lg, font-medium.
- **Rule**: Never place two amber buttons side by side.

### Cards
- Standard: `rounded-xl border border-fd-border bg-fd-background p-5`
- Interactive: Add `group hover:border-accent-warm hover:shadow-sm hover:-translate-y-0.5`
- In docs content: use Fumadocs `<Card>` and `<Cards>` components for consistent styling

### Icons
- Heroicons outline style, 24x24 viewBox, `h-8 w-8 text-accent-warm`, `strokeWidth={1.5}`

### Texture Effects
- `hero-grain`: CSS noise overlay (3% light / 6% dark). Used on hero and final CTA ONLY.
- `hero-gradient`: Radial gradients (warm amber top, purple bottom-right). Subtle, never competes with text.
- Content inside grain sections must have `relative z-10` to sit above the pseudo-element.

### Dark Mode
- All custom colors have explicit dark overrides in `global.css`.
- Amber is brighter in dark mode. Stage colors boosted 5-10% lightness.
- Always test changes in both modes.

### Sidebar
- Stage section headings get colored dots matching their IDEAL stage color (via `SidebarSeparator` component)
- Sidebar items show progress state: green checkmark (completed), lock icon (locked), dot (unlocked/unread)
- Locked items are dimmed and non-clickable
- `defaultOpenLevel: 1` keeps stage folders expanded by default

### Progress Gating
- Sequential reading enforced: page N+1 unlocks only when page N is completed
- Completion trigger: scrolling to 85% of page depth
- Storage: localStorage (`tvp-progress`) + cookie (`tvp-progress`)
- First page (`/docs`) is always unlocked
- Locked pages show a lock icon, message, and "Continue where you left off" CTA before redirecting
- Progress state managed via `ProgressProvider` context in `lib/progress.tsx`

### Bottom Navigation
- Custom prev/next cards replace the Fumadocs default footer (`footer: { enabled: false }`)
- Each card shows title + description (from frontmatter)
- "Next" card uses stage accent color on border and title
- Cards have hover lift effect (`hover:-translate-y-0.5`)
- Order follows `lib/reading-order.ts` canonical sequence, not filesystem order

### Checklist for Editing Content Pages
- [ ] No duplicate H1 (frontmatter title handles it)
- [ ] No publisher/internal metadata (back cover, pitches, author notes)
- [ ] Uses `<Callout>` for key concepts and rules
- [ ] Uses `<Cards>` + `<Card>` for navigation grids and overviews
- [ ] Bold labels follow manuscript patterns for auto-detection
- [ ] Links to other pages use relative paths (`/docs/stage-1-identify/friction-scan`)
- [ ] `full: true` in frontmatter if using Cards or wide layouts
- [ ] No em dashes
- [ ] Tested visually in browser after changes
- [ ] Design decisions documented in this file and DESIGN-SYSTEM.md